# Attestation

Attestation is the process of comparing workload measurements and configuration against the set of policies.
On successful attestation a signed token is generated to indicate the workload's compliance.
In absence of policies in the request, attestation evaluates policies associated with the API client.
Along with user specified policies, the default policy which attests the enclave's measurement is always evaluated.

## Attest

### POST /appraisal/v1/attest

The Appraisal API attests the submitted evidence and policies. A signed JWT Attestation Token is returned upon
successful verification. In case of attestation failure, appropriate error message is returned.

#### Parameters

| Parameters                     |                                       |
|--------------------------------|---------------------------------------|
| Content-Type  (required)       | Content-Type header                   |
|                                | Available values :   application/json |
|                                | string (header)                       |
| Accept  (required)             | Accept header                         |
|                                | Available values :   application/json |
|                                | string (header)                       |

Parameter content type:
application/json

  "event_log": "[ { \"rtmr\": {  \"index\":1....",
  "init_time_data": [
    0
  ],
  "nonce": {
    "iat": "MjAyMi0wNy0wNSAwOTozOToxOS4zNTEwNTM2NiArMDAwMCBVVEM=",
    "signature": "",
    "val": "YKrm2nC9bZQLstn+ABSP6LCu4TcyU3evGx+Cc1uRRkqoq4Vf6qyQNlnNIs/BpiKs/ZWYV73xxexFU+O4PRzUXQ=="
  },
  "policy_ids": [
    "0cbe2738-aaac-4d8a-a8c3-181ba1e5961c",
    "4985d7fd-2b7e-4d7d-82a9-99f2c35da6e1"

#### Responses

Response content type: application/json

| Code | Description                        |
|-----|-------------------------------------|
| 400 | Invalid request body.               |
| 403 | RBAC access denied.                 |
| 415 | Invalid Content-Type/Accept header. |
| 500 | Internal server error.              |

## Nonce

### GET /appraisal/v1/nonce

Responsible for generating a nonce to be sent to attestation client during quote generation.
The nonce is a signed base64 string with random 64 bytes and issued timestamp.

#### Parameters

| Parameters                     |                                       |
|--------------------------------|---------------------------------------|
| Accept  (required)             | Accept header                         |
|                                | Available values :   application/json |
|                                | string (header)                       |

#### Responses

Response content type: application/json

| Code | Description                       |
|------|-----------------------------------|
| 200  | Successfully generated Nonce.     |
| 403  | RBAC access denied                |
| 415  | Invalid Accept Header in Request. |
| 500  | Internal server error.            |

Example Response Value:

```json
{
  "iat": "MjAyMi0wNy0wNSAwOTozOToxOS4zNTEwNTM2NiArMDAwMCBVVEM=",
  "signature": "",
  "val": "YKrm2nC9bZQLstn+ABSP6LCu4TcyU3evGx+Cc1uRRkqoq4Vf6qyQNlnNIs/BpiKs/ZWYV73xxexFU+O4PRzUXQ=="
}
```
